;Monomer proteins at 18 mg/ml in 20 mM TRIS/HCl, pH 8.0, 150 mM NaCl, 10% glycerol 5 mM DTT were mixed with an equal volume of the precipitant solution, and then suspend over 0.25 ml of precipitant solution. Leaf-shaped hexagonal crystals grew to up to 0.4 mm on a side after a period of two weeks. Crystals were frozen by transferring them, in six sequential steps, to a solution containing 0.1M Bis-Tris Propane, pH 7.5, 0.2M potassium thiocyanate, 20% PEG 3350 and 20% glycerol.
;
